                            <comment id="468343" author="adilger" created="Wed, 20 Aug 2025 19:52:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As I look at these functions, I also notice that there is no man page for &lt;tt&gt;llapi_changelog_repack_rec()&lt;/tt&gt; that was added in patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/50099&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/50099&lt;/a&gt; (&quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13308&quot; title=&quot;update changelog_ext_nid to handle IPv6 addresses&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-13308&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-13308&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; mdd: add LLOG_F_EXT_X_NID_BE&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="468339" author="adilger" created="Wed, 20 Aug 2025 19:43:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Etienne, I was going to point someone at the Changelog man pages that you previously added in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12837&quot; title=&quot;man pages for llapi_changelog_start() and all other llapi_changelog_*() functions&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-12837&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-12837&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to help them understand &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs changelog&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; output and what records are returned via &quot;&lt;tt&gt;llapi_changelog_recv()&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;, but I don&apos;t see a description of the different Changelog records (or the ASCII formatted versions printed by &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs changelog&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;) anywhere in these man pages or in the Lustre manual.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Would you be able to update the &lt;tt&gt;llapi_changelog_recv.3&lt;/tt&gt; man page to describe &lt;tt&gt;struct changelog_rec&lt;/tt&gt; and the various fields/flags/constants therein?  It looks like the &lt;tt&gt;CHANGELOG_FLAG&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;CHANGELOG_EXTRA_FLAG&lt;/tt&gt; are defined in &lt;tt&gt;llapi_changelog_start.3&lt;/tt&gt;, but there would need to be a description of what these flags mean for decoding &lt;tt&gt;changelog_rec&lt;/tt&gt; in &lt;tt&gt;llapi_changelog_recv.3&lt;/tt&gt;.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That also makes me wonder if we should add a new llapi &quot;wrapper&quot; function that hides the details of FLAGS vs. EXTRA_FLAGS and decoding of the changelog records?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
